<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" FontFamily="Calibri">
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Overview</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Fretboard is a main component used by application. Here user can select position by clicking on particular fret and string to view the note
    Fretboard component takes part in most of excercies as well as in selection.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Structure</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Fretboard component reflects real finger board of 4-string bass guitar. It has 4 string names E,A,D,G (from bottom) and there are 15 frets
  	 availabl. However only 12 are in the scope of application.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontSize="24">Behavior</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>When no excercise is running then user can freely click on any position to get
    information of selected position as : what note is it, how it sound etc. When excercise is run and fretboard takes part in it then either note is shown
    on fretboard and no interaction with user is expected or user can select position on fretboard to check if provided anwser is correct.
    </Paragraph>

</FlowDocument>